Package: mediation
Version: 1.0
Date: 2008-11-01
Title: R Package for Causal Mediation Analysis
Author: Luke Keele <keele.4@polisci.osu.edu>,
        Dustin Tingley <dtingley@princeton.edu>,
        Teppei Yamamoto <tyamamot@princeton.edu>,
        Kosuke Imai <kimai@princeton.edu>.
Maintainer: Luke Keele <keele.4@polisci.osu.edu>
Depends: R (>= 2.8)
Description: mediation is a publicly available R package that allows
both parametric and nonparametric causal mediation analysis.  It
implements the methods and suggestions of in Imai, Keele, and Yamamoto
(2008) ``Identification and Inference in Causal Mediation Analysis.''
In addition to the estimation of the average causal mediation effects,
the software also allows researchers to conduct sensitivity analyses
in both parametric and nonparametric settings.
LazyLoad: yes
LazyData: yes
License: GPL (version 2 or later)
